      "created_at": "2024-04-28T19:10:08.860Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I noticed a recent change in behaviour in the mobile app.  When I select a workout the display shows Target Power (row 3, col 1).  As soon as my heart rate monitor connects the same cell (row 3, col1) switches over to Target Heart Rate.  Not too long ago, this always showed target power.</p>\n<p>I do understand the convenience of switching over to Target Heart Rate when the HR monitor is attached (and so this is not a \u201cbug\u201d), but I\u2019m in a unique situation.  I have a spin bike purchased 2nd hand. It has a power hub that connects to a head unit through an old (and I believe proprietary) wireless connection.  So TD does not detect the power hub.  That\u2019s been fine since I would just follow along matching the Power on the head unit to TD\u2019s Target Power.  But now that that is no longer showing, I can\u2019t follow along.</p>\n<p>I look thru the app options, but I didn\u2019t see an option to keep Target Power showing regardless.</p>\n<p>Thanks for your help</p>",
